        <heading>Section </heading>
        <content>
          <p>SECTION 2.  ACCEPTANCE
Art. 957.  Formal or informal acceptance
Acceptance may be either formal or informal.  It is formal when the successor expressly accepts in writing or assumes the quality of successor in a judicial proceeding.  It is informal when the successor does some act that clearly implies his intention to accept.</p>
        </content>
